<P>&nbsp;</P>
<B><P>Power Functions</P>
</B>
<P>Linear functions and quadratic functions are particular power functions.  In a linear function the highest value of the power is 1.   In a quadratic function the highest value of the power is 2.</P>

<P>A cubic function has the general form f(x) = ax<SUP>3</SUP> + bx<SUP>2</SUP> + cx + d.   It is a power function of degree 3.</P>

<P>It is possible to have power functions which have higher values in the power of the variable than 3.   The power may also take a fractional value or a negative value.   Read through pages 10 – 13 of your notes. </P></FONT></BODY>
